OL,3,CReplica of Spitfire destroyed in head-
OL,4,Con WW2 crash revealed
OL,6,FA replica of a Spitfire destroyed in a
OL,7,Fhead-on crash in Northumberland will
OL,8,Fbe housed at its former base to mark
OL,9,F80 years since its pilot's death.
OL,11,FSupermarine Spitfire Mk IA R6762 was
OL,12,Fpart of a training unit based in
OL,13,FEshott, Northumberland, when it
OL,14,Fcollided with an American Thunderbolt
OL,15,Fin 12 April 1944.
OL,17,FThe new model made in the craft's
OL,18,Fimage will be unveiled at
OL,19,FNorthumberland Woodland Burial and
OL,20,FCrematorium, which was once part of
OL,21,FRAF Eshott.
