OL,4,Con WW2 crash revealed
OL,6,FThe Thunderbolt pilot, First
OL,7,FLieutenant Serapiglia, based at RAF
OL,8,FMilfield, had disobeyed orders and was
OL,9,Fflying in the opposite direction. He
OL,10,Fcollided head on with the Spitfire.
OL,12,FThe craft was engulfed in flames and
OL,13,Fcrashed at Blawearie Field at Eshott
OL,14,FHome Farm.
OL,16,FFirst Lieutenant Serapliglia died when
OL,17,Fhis plane lost a wing and burst into
OL,18,Fflames. It crashed south of Eshott
OL,19,FAirfield.
