OL,3,CReplica of Spitfire destroyed in head-
OL,4,Con WW2 crash revealed
OL,6,FLaura Clarehugh of Northumberland
OL,7,FWoodland Burials and Crematorium,
OL,8,Fsaid: "We're incredibly proud of our
OL,9,FNorthumbrian heritage. We felt it was
OL,10,Freally important to honour the memory
OL,11,Fof those that served here.
OL,13,F"It's our great privilege to have a
OL,14,Freplica of R6762 to not only
OL,15,Fcommemorate Sergeant Knagenhjelm and
OL,16,FFirst Lieutenant Serapiglia, but all
OL,17,Fthose that served during the war."
